cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language processing and machine learning, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper specifically deals with obtaining class membership probabilities, which is a common problem in machine learning, suggesting that cs.LG is a likely category. The paper also presents experiments to measure the accuracy of the probabilistic classifier, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with text chunking, which is a task related to information retrieval, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
